  this relationship between continuous current and discharge time is stable and absolute,
  but real batteries don''t behave exactly as this simple linear formula would indicate.  Therefore,
  when amp-hour capacity is given for a battery, it is specified at either a given
  current, given time, or assumed to be rated for a time period of 8 hours (if no
  limiting factor is given).

